author: Carolyn King
title: CIBC Profit Increases, Despite Struggling Canadian Economy
text:
Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce on Thursday reported a higher profit for the fiscal third quarter, joining other Canadian banks which have reported so far this earnings season in shrugging off the effects of a stumbling Canadian economy.
Toronto-based CIBC said it had net income of 978 million Canadian dollars ($734 million), or C$2.42 a share, in the quarter ended July 31. That was up from C$921 million, or C$2.26, a year...
